        <description>
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Cross-Reference Guide Overview</title>
                <para>
                    This training module provides comprehensive guidance on creating and managing 
                    cross-references within the AMPEL360 Q100 documentation ecosystem. Proper 
                    cross-referencing ensures traceability, maintains document integrity, and 
                    facilitates navigation across the complex network of technical documentation.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Purpose:</emphasis> To standardize reference 
                    management practices across SSOT artifacts, S1000D data modules, and DPP integration.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Scope:</emphasis> Internal references, cross-DM 
                    references, SSOT artifact references, DPP integration, traceability matrices, 
                    and CI/CD validation.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Internal References (internalRef)</title>
                <para>
                    Internal references link to content within the same S1000D Data Module using 
                    the internalRef element.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Syntax:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;internalRef internalRefId="target-id" 
             internalRefTargetType="irtt01"&gt;
  Link Text
&lt;/internalRef&gt;

Where:
  target-id = Unique ID of target element (@id attribute)
  irtt01 = Inline reference type (S1000D standard)
                    </verbatimText>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Example:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;!-- Define target --&gt;
&lt;para id="term-bwb"&gt;
  BWB (Blended Wing Body) is an aircraft configuration...
&lt;/para&gt;

&lt;!-- Reference from elsewhere --&gt;
&lt;para&gt;
  For more information, see 
  &lt;internalRef internalRefId="term-bwb" 
               internalRefTargetType="irtt01"&gt;BWB definition&lt;/internalRef&gt;.
&lt;/para&gt;
                    </verbatimText>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Best Practices:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <randomList>
                        <listItem><para>Use descriptive ID values (term-bwb, fig-fuel-cell-diagram)</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>Ensure all target IDs are unique within the DM</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>Use consistent naming conventions for IDs</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>Validate all internal references before publication</para></listItem>
                    </randomList>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Cross-DM References (dmRef)</title>
                <para>
                    Cross-DM references link to other S1000D Data Modules using the dmRef element 
                    with complete DMC resolution.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Syntax:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;dmRef&gt;
  &lt;dmRefIdent&gt;
    &lt;dmCode modelIdentCode="AMPEL360" 
            systemDiffCode="00" 
            systemCode="00" 
            subSystemCode="0" 
            subSubSystemCode="0" 
            assyCode="00" 
            disassyCode="00" 
            disassyCodeVariant="A" 
            infoCode="001" 
            infoCodeVariant="A" 
            itemLocationCode="A"/&gt;
  &lt;/dmRefIdent&gt;
  &lt;dmRefAddressItems&gt;
    &lt;dmTitle&gt;
      &lt;techName&gt;Program Glossary&lt;/techName&gt;
    &lt;/dmTitle&gt;
  &lt;/dmRefAddressItems&gt;
&lt;/dmRef&gt;
                    </verbatimText>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Common Q100 Cross-References:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry>DMC</entry>
                                <entry>Title</entry>
                                <entry>Usage</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>DMC-AMPEL360-00-00-00-00A-001A-A</entry>
                                <entry>Program Glossary</entry>
                                <entry>Term definitions</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>DMC-AMPEL360-00-00-00-00A-042A-A</entry>
                                <entry>Term Type Usage Guide</entry>
                                <entry>Terminology guidance</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>DMC-AMPEL360-00-00-00-00A-044A-A</entry>
                                <entry>Safety Labeling Standard</entry>
                                <entry>Warning/caution formats</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>SSOT Artifact References</title>
                <para>
                    SSOT artifacts (requirements, analyses, tests) use URI-based references for 
                    cross-linking.
                </para>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>KNU URI Scheme</title>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
knu://{KNU-ID}[#{section}]

Examples:
  knu://KNU-00-00-001-REQ-001
  knu://KNU-28-00-001-REQ-001#section-3.2
  knu://KNU-71-00-001-ICD-001#interface-definition
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>Term URI Scheme</title>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
term://{term-id}

Examples:
  term://bwb
  term://lh2
  term://fuel-cell
  term://learning-assurance
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>DPP Integration References</title>
                <para>
                    Digital Product Passport (DPP) integration uses ampel360: URI scheme for 
                    component and data references.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">URI Patterns:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
ampel360:term:{term-id}
ampel360:unit:{unit-id}
ampel360:component:{serial-number}
ampel360:batch:{batch-id}

Examples:
  ampel360:term:bwb
  ampel360:unit:kilogram
  ampel360:component:FC-001-2026-001
  ampel360:batch:LH2-TANK-BATCH-2026-Q1
                    </verbatimText>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Usage in S1000D:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;externalPubRef&gt;
  &lt;externalPubRefIdent&gt;
    &lt;externalPubCode&gt;ampel360:term:bwb&lt;/externalPubCode&gt;
  &lt;/externalPubRefIdent&gt;
&lt;/externalPubRef&gt;
                    </verbatimText>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Traceability Matrix Usage</title>
                <para>
                    Traceability matrices establish formal relationships between requirements, 
                    designs, tests, and verification evidence.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Matrix Structure:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="5">
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Requirement ID</entry>
                                <entry>Design KNU</entry>
                                <entry>Test KNU</entry>
                                <entry>Verification Evidence</entry>
                                <entry>Status</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>KNU-28-00-001-REQ-001</entry>
                                <entry>KNU-28-00-001-ICD-001</entry>
                                <entry>KNU-28-00-001-TEST-001</entry>
                                <entry>TR-28-001-v1.2.pdf</entry>
                                <entry>VERIFIED</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>KNU-71-00-001-REQ-002</entry>
                                <entry>KNU-71-00-001-ICD-002</entry>
                                <entry>KNU-71-00-001-TEST-002</entry>
                                <entry>TR-71-002-v1.0.pdf</entry>
                                <entry>IN-PROGRESS</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Mandatory Traces:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <randomList>
                        <listItem><para>REQ → ICD (requirement to design)</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>REQ → TEST (requirement to verification)</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>ICD → PUB (design to publication)</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>TEST → Evidence (test to results)</para></listItem>
                    </randomList>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Link Validation in CI/CD Pipeline</title>
                <para>
                    The Q100 CI/CD pipeline automatically validates all cross-references using 
                    GitHub Actions workflows.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Validation Checks:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <randomList>
                        <listItem><para>Internal reference targets exist</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>Cross-DM references resolve to valid DMCs</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>KNU references point to existing artifacts</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>Term references exist in terminology database</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>Traceability matrix completeness</para></listItem>
                    </randomList>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Workflow Files:</emphasis>
                </para>
                <para>
                    <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
.github/workflows/markdown-link-check.yml
.github/workflows/knu-collision-check.yml
.github/workflows/brex-validation.yml
                    </verbatimText>
                </para>
                <para>
                    Validation runs automatically on pull requests. Failed validation blocks merge.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Best Practices for Reference Integrity</title>
                <para>
                    Follow these practices to maintain reference integrity:
                </para>
                <para>
                    <sequentialList>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Use Stable IDs:</emphasis> Never 
                            change IDs after publication. If renaming is necessary, create new ID 
                            and maintain redirect.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Validate Before Commit:</emphasis> 
                            Run local validation before committing. Use provided validation scripts 
                            in tools/ directory.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Document Dependencies:</emphasis> 
                            In KNU YAML frontmatter, list all parent and child KNUs, related KNOTs, 
                            and ATA traces.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Update Traceability Matrices:</emphasis> 
                            When creating or modifying REQ/ICD/TEST KNUs, update corresponding 
                            traceability matrix.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Use Relative Paths in SSOT:</emphasis> 
                            For SSOT-to-SSOT references, use relative filesystem paths when 
                            possible to support repository reorganization.</para>
                        </listItem>
                    </sequentialList>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Common Mistakes and Corrections</title>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Mistake</entry>
                                <entry>Problem</entry>
                                <entry>Correction</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Hardcoded absolute paths</entry>
                                <entry>Breaks on repository reorganization</entry>
                                <entry>Use relative paths or URI schemes</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Missing target IDs</entry>
                                <entry>References break silently</entry>
                                <entry>Always define @id on referenceable elements</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Duplicate IDs</entry>
                                <entry>Ambiguous references</entry>
                                <entry>Ensure all IDs unique within DM scope</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Broken cross-DM refs after DMC update</entry>
                                <entry>References point to old version</entry>
                                <entry>Update all referencing DMs when DMC changes</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </levelledPara>
            
